        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 20 at 9:22PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 921 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Craigsville to 8 miles southwest of
Summersville. These thunderstorms are nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph, pea size hail, and very heavy
rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Summersville, Camden-On-gauley, Camden On Gauley, Craigsville,
Calvin, Kesslers Cross Lanes, Canvas, Nettie, and Mount Nebo.

This includes Route 19 between mile markers 31 and 45.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
